<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3823] Add a field-filtering FilterAtomicReader to 4.0 so ParallelReaders can be better tested (in LTC.maybeWrapReader)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3823</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;In addition to the filters in contrib/misc for horizontally filtering (by doc-id) AtomicReader, it would be good to have the same vertically (by field). For now I will add this implementation to test-framework, as it cannot stay in contrib/misc, because LTC will need it for maybeWrapReader.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;LTC will use this FilterAtomicReader to construct a ParallelAtomicReader out of two (or maybe more) FieldFilterAtomicReaders.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
